          "date": "2013-11-19 09:23:28.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-3717 llite: check whether parent is NULL in ll_encode_fh()",
        "message": "LU-3717 llite: check whether parent is NULL in ll_encode_fh()\n\nSince Linux kernel 2.6.39, the open by handle system calls\nhave been added. In fs/fhandle.c, exportfs_encode_fh() is\ncalled with connectable=0, which makes parent=NULL passed\nto ll_encode_fh(). This patch checks the value of parent\nin ll_encode_fh() before running ll_inode2fid(parent)\nso as to avoid the ASSERTION( inode != ((void *)0) ) failure.\n\nTest-Parameters: testlist=parallel-scale-nfsv3,parallel-scale-nfsv4\n\nSigned-off-by: Jian Yu <jian.yu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I97bf5386f5f59ea70f87b26e1e34be4a2565fa5d\n"
      },
